A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Healthcare Quality and Reporting; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, healthcare quality, cost, and accessibility are key concerns for the residents of
4 Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, the establishment of a standardized healthcare reporting initiative aims to
6 measure and improve the quality of healthcare services across the state; and
7 WHEREAS, a comprehensive system for collecting, analyzing, and reporting clinical and
8 claims data can improve patient outcomes and reduce overall healthcare costs; and
9 WHEREAS, integrating electronic health records and claims data will enhance transparency
10 in healthcare services, improve substance use disorder treatment, and foster clinical research
11 in Georgia; and
12 WHEREAS, it is essential to examine the implications of healthcare reporting on providers,
13 Medicaid recipients, and insurance entities operating in Georgia; and
