38 (B) The Speaker of the House of Representatives shall appoint five members of the
39 House of Representatives.
40 (C) The Speaker shall also appoint an additional four nonlegislative members of the
41 committee as follows:
42 (i) One representative from the Georgia Department of Community Health;
43 (ii) One representative from a statewide healthcare data initiative;
44 (iii) One practicing healthcare data analyst; and
45 (iv) One representative from a Medicaid care management organization.
46 (D) The Speaker shall also designate a legislative member of the committee as
47 chairperson of the committee.
48 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
49 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
50 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
51 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee. The committee
52 may conduct such meetings at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or
53 convenient to enable it to exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and
54 accomplish the objectives and purposes of this resolution.
55 (5) Allowances, expenses, and funding.
56 (A) The legislative members of the committee shall receive the allowances provided
57 for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated.
58 (B) Members of the committee who are state officials, other than legislative members,
59 or who are state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the
60 committee, but they may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the
61 performance of their duties as members of the committee in the same manner as they
62 are reimbursed for expenses in their capacities as state officials or employees.
63 (C) Members of the committee who are not legislators, state officials, or state
64 employees shall receive a daily expense allowance in an amount the same as that
